      "side": 1,
      "message": "Previously, we had a mechanism to convert app-status errors to gRPC errors in postlude. if we return a gRPC errors directly in a handler, it will be converted to an internal error because there\u0027s no associated app status.\nI needed a utility function to convert gRPC error to app-status error so I can selectively preserve some gRPC errors by converting them to app-status error first.\nin https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/infra/luci/luci-go/+/2586406, vadim suggested that we should convert the errors in the handlers instead. As a result, this is no longer needed.",
      "parentUuid": "4efd4d9e_f3976e81",
      "revId": "46152f203ba962204ad61e1b56f3828a2c6969bb",
